"{\"uid\": \"si.com-olympics-simone-biles-jonathan-owens-sweet-quote-paris-olympics\", \"text\": \"In this story:  Chicago Bears safety Jonathan Owens is grateful his team is letting him miss part of the preseason sohe can travel to Paris to cheer on his wife, four-time gold medal gymnast Simone Biles, in the Olympics.  Owens will miss one practice session, a walkthrough and the Hall of Fame Game vs. the Houston Texans while he's in Paris. But, he would not miss supporting Biles for the world.  \\u00e2\\u0080\\u009cIt\\u00e2\\u0080\\u0099s amazing,\\u00e2\\u0080\\u009d Owens said,viaNBC Sports Chicago. \\u00e2\\u0080\\u009cWords can\\u00e2\\u0080\\u0099t even describe it. I just think about, \\u00e2\\u0080\\u0098How did I get so lucky that this is my wife and I get to see her, someone that\\u00e2\\u0080\\u0099s literally at the pinnacle of their sport, and I get to call this my wife?\\u00e2\\u0080\\u0099 It\\u00e2\\u0080\\u0099s amazing. There\\u00e2\\u0080\\u0099s no words to really describe it. Just blessed.\\u00e2\\u0080\\u009d  Owens, who signed with the Bears after one season with the Green Bay Packers, praised the Bears for being understanding about him missing time with the team to go to the Olympics.  \\\"It was something me and my agent talked about when we went in and I signed with the team,\\\" Owens said,\\u00c2viaThe Associated Press. \\\"It was all respectful. We went to them and just asked, 'We would really appreciate it if he could go and support his wife,' and they were really cool about it. First-class organization. I just want to thank them so much for allowing me to go over and do that. I can not wait to be able to support her, and I know my family and my wife, she really appreciates it.\\\"  Biles's Olympic run begins on Sunday, July 28 with the qualifying round. She won gold in the team, all-around, vault and floor exercise during the 2016 Rio Olympics.  Loading recommendations... Please wait while we load personalized content recommendations  